abstract we study a model of strategic experimentation motivated by collective decision making with costly information acquisiti page 1 abstract we study a model of strategic experimentation motivated by collective decision making with costly information acquisition or r&d and the innovation process when the outcomes of experimentation are publicly observable free riding results in inefficiently low experimentation at equilibrium however when a third party the information aggregator holds all the information and commits when to reveal it efficiency increases we construct the unique symmetric markovian equilibrium of the underlying game and solve for the optimal revelation time we also discuss comparative statics with respect to the number of participating agents and several interesting extensions
